history.text: Did you like Robert Downey Jr. as Iron Man?
I did!  I thought he played the role flawlessly.  Can you believe that this movie came out in 2008?
I thought he was a great choice for the character and I couldn't imagine anyone doing a better job. What about you?
Yeah seems like just yesterday to me.
He was superb!  Do you think that he played the role well enough to make if feel like his character could actually play out in every day life?
I really enjoyed watching Jeff Bridges too. Been far too long since he'd gotten a really good role. He's awesome.
Yeah, I could see Iron Man being a real person. Wish I could be him!
He is awesome.  Always can add a flare.  How do you feel Gwyneth Paltrow played Pepper Pots?
Ah, Pepper Pots. She did well. I could see other actresses doing just as good a job but overall I enjoyed her performance as well.
The movie even got great critic reviews.
As was deserved!

Anything 
in particular that you disliked?
Not really?  I am not the biggest superhero movie fan.  Although, this movie I truly liked.  It kept you at the edge of your chair.  What about you?
I can't remember anything that I disliked.
It's strange to say that because I enjoy Superhero movies alot and I've watched them all and can be very critical at times. But this movie is almost flawless.
Wow- thorough critic!  Had a good perception of the movie.  Wouldn't you agree?
From start to finish you're engaged and you get a sense that Iron Man is human and has flaws but it's fun to see him overcome them, while keeping his sense or humor and spunk.
of*
I do also think that director did give the movie a military theme.  It kinda had a strict undertone
Also the CG was amazing!!!
Yes the military presence is there. Didn't detract from the film imo though.

I was also impressed how real the movie seemed.  Very good CG.  It made you believe
 that Iron man was something someone could truly create.
Yes it did. I agree with you.

The movie had such an intriguing
 story line.
I compare Tony Stark to Elon Musk!  LOL
Yes, and I feel it's hard to have intriguing story lines when it comes to superhero movies.
Haha yeah Ole Musky could def be a Tony Stark in real life!
I don't think I became bored at all during the movie.  Such a unique plot.
Interesting comparison. Both super smart, geniuses with lots of money and power.
If you could be Tony Stark would you?
Heck yes!  What about you?  To have that power to better the world would be a magnificent gift!
While I'd most definitely say yes and I agree with your previous statement I can't help but think it would be incredibly hard to live his life.
Do you think they made the plot believable that a human could unleash a massive electrical surge on towards someone else?
Not only does he have a huge responsibility now but after the shards made their way into his body he is constantly reminded that he could die at any moment.
You mean the EMP? that's possible already...
I feel compelled to ask you if you're real or AI?
I am real
I am real
Is Tony Stark real?
Do you think someone could build a suit like Tony starks?
No, not yet but maybe one day. Do you?
Maybe one day.  Maybe not to the level that his is though.
Yeah highly doubt it too.
Been a pleasure! Have a great rest of your day real AI person or user. :)

Do you think Tony Stark made a good move admitting
 he is Iron Man to the public?
Yes, good move!
Same to you.  I am most Def.  a person
A mturker!
I believe you, same here!
Haha Later
